precise_thumbnails.hint_1: Set the storage time for precise screenshots of face recognition/ANPR events in this field. The object that triggered the detector is guaranteed to be present on the precise screenshot. These screenshots are displayed on the {events_link} page.
precise_thumbnails.hint_2: Attention to the system administrator: the precise screenshots are stored in Flussonic Watcher database. Make sure your system complies with the {requirements_link}.
precise_thumbnails.hint_3: If disabled or the precise screenshot storage time expires but there is an archive for the period, then the first frame of the five-second video segment in which the event occurred is displayed on the {events_link} page. In this case, the object that triggered the detector may be present at any place in the video fragment, so you will have to search for it manually.
